<p />
<h1><a name="Introduction"> Introduction </a></h1>
<p />
XML is a <span style='background : #FFFFCE;'><font color="#0000FF">GoodThing</font></span><a href="/twiki/bin/edit/Main/GoodThing?topicparent=Main.XmlForHumans">?</a>.  Writing it by hand <strike>often</strike> usually is not.
<p />
The same could be said for HTML, SGML, and all the other markup cousins.
<p />
Could wiki-simplicity be brought to XML for humans?
<p />
<h1><a name="Resources"> Resources </a></h1>
<p />
<ul>
<li> Humans should not have to grok XML - <a href="http://www-106.ibm.com/developerworks/xml/library/x-sbxml.html" target="_top">http://www-106.ibm.com/developerworks/xml/library/x-sbxml.html</a>
</li>
<li> SXML: Scheme and XML - <a href="http://okmij.org/ftp/Scheme/xml.html" target="_top">http://okmij.org/ftp/Scheme/xml.html</a>
</li>
<li> SOX: Simple Outline XML - <a href="http://www.langdale.com.au/SOX/" target="_top">http://www.langdale.com.au/SOX/</a>
</li>
<li> <span style='background : #FFFFCE;'><font color="#0000FF">SLiP</font></span><a href="/twiki/bin/edit/Main/SLiP?topicparent=Main.XmlForHumans">?</a>: a "Sorta Like Python" shorthand for XML - <a href="http://www.scottsweeney.com/projects/slip" target="_top">http://www.scottsweeney.com/projects/slip</a>
</li>
<li> xsltxt: An alternative xslt syntax - <a href="http://www.zanthan.com/ajm/xsltxt/" target="_top">http://www.zanthan.com/ajm/xsltxt/</a>
</li>
</ul>
<p />
-- <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/LesOrchard">LesOrchard</a> - 05 Apr 2002
